  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Cambridge Bible for Schools and Colleges",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and there abode three months",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] More literally, with ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Rev. Ver.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", “",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and when he had spent three months there",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ",” connecting it, as the Greek does, with what follows.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "and when the Jews laid wait for him",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] The English of the A.V. defines too precisely the form of the danger. Read “",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And when a plot was laid against him by the Jews",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".” The Jews, who had tried to engage Gallio in their matters on St Paul’s last visit to Corinth, now take a secret instead of a public means of wreaking their vengeance on him. And we may judge that St Paul anticipated some trouble from the Judaizing party at Corinth by the tone of the latter portion (after chap. 9) of his second Epistle written to them while he was on his way, but detained in Macedonia. There were persons in Corinth who spoke slightingly of the Apostle. His bodily presence was weak and his speech contemptible. And in opposition to the remarks of these opponents, the Epistle concludes with an assertion of St Paul’s equality to the chiefest Apostles, a recital more full than in any other place of his sufferings for the Gospel, and an account of revelations divinely made unto him. It is clear therefore that among those who would be counted as Christians St Paul was not everywhere accepted. The Jews under such circumstances would have some abettors in their animosity even among the Judæo-Christians, and seem to have planned some means whereby St Paul might be attacked on his sea-voyage to Syria. No doubt the intention was to kill him. The word in the original is that used (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 9:24",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") when the Jews watched the gates of Damascus night and day to kill him.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "as he was about to sail into Syria",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] The rendering of the ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Rev. Ver.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " gives the sense more vividly “",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "as he was about to set sail for Syria",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".” He had apparently gone so far as to arrange for his passage and go on board, and was nearly departed, before he got the warning news. Perhaps some heart, among the people to whom the plot was known on shore, was moved to give a hint of the great peril at the last moment. This is the more probable if we suppose some previous communications between the Jews and the Judaizers among the Christians.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "he purposed to return through Macedonia",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "] Better, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "bld",
        "text": "he determined",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", with ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Rev. Ver.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " As the scheme for killing him had been meant to be carried out at sea, the choice of an overland journey and a prompt departure made the forming of a new plan impossible to the conspirators.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Bengel's Gnomen",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 20:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "Ποιήσας",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") The nominative was employed by Luke before that the predicate (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἐγένετο γνώμη",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") occurred to him, which requires the oblique case (viz. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "αὐτῷ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Such constructions are found not only in Hebrew, but also in Greek and Latin writers.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "μῆνας τρεῖς",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "three months",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") at which time also he seems to have seen the Corinthians, but only ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "in passing",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ": ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Corinthians 16:7",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "αὐτῷ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "μέλλοντι ἀνάγεσθαι",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "for him, as he was about to sail",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") They were laying plots for Paul against this very journey to Syria.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "εἰς τὴν Συρίαν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "into Syria",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") ch. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 21:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ".—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἐγένετο γνώμη",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "he determined",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") Sometimes they relied on a, general, sometimes on a special call.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ὑποστρέφειν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "to return",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") Even a holy purpose can sometimes be changed. Comp. ch. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 19:21",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", where Paul is represented as having once wished to go through Macedonia. It appears that Paul had wished, after journeying through Macedonia and Achaia, to go forward to Jerusalem. But at that time, indeed, lie did not get to Jerusalem, but again returned through Macedonia. His journey to Jerusalem, and to Rome afterwards, proceeded (was accomplished) by another way: the order merely of his course being changed.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 3.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "- When he had spent ... there",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " for ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "there abode",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", A.V.; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "a plot was laid against him by the Jews",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " for ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "when the Jews laid wait for him",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", A.V.; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "for",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " for ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "into",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", A.V.; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "determined",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " for ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "purposed",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", A.V. (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ἐγένετο γνώμης",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", R.T.). ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "When he had spent three months",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". For this use of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ποιεῖν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", see ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 15:33",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ":33. See also ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Corinthians 11:25",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", where the R.V. varies the rendering, and seems to take ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ποιεῖν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " as a verb neuter, as the A.V. does here, the accusative (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "μῆνας τρεῖς",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") being taken as that of time how long. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "And a plot",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", etc. There is no \"and\" in the Greek. It is better to take the T.R., and to consider ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ποιήσας",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " as a ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "nominative pendens",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " as ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ἐπιγνόντες",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " is in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 19:34",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", according to the reading of Meyer, Alford, etc. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "A plot was laid against him by the Jews",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". It appears from this that Apollos had not succeeded in subduing the bigoted hatred of the Corinthian Jews. But probably the desperate measure of a plot against his life (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ἐπιβουλή",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", as in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 9:23, 24",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ver. 19 of this chapter, and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Acts 23:30",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") is an indication that many of their number had joined the Church; and that the unbelieving remnant, being foiled in argument, had recourse to violence. He ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "determined",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; literally, according to the R.T., ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "he was of opinion.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " But the T.R. has ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "ἐγένετο γνώμη",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", \"his opinion was,\" the construction of the sentence being changed. The three months were probably chiefly spent at Corinth, according to the intention expressed in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Corinthians 16:6",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", though it would seem that he had stayed a longer time in Macedonia than he anticipated. It was during his sojourn at Corinth that the Epistle to the Romans was written. Acts 20:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
